The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of neural network inference, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses using classification error to remove parts of the network, which falls under the category of neural network optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper mentions using Gumbel reparameterization, which is a technique commonly used in reinforcement learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses experimental results for ImageNet classification, which is a common benchmark dataset in natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
